				<td colspan="2"><span>You know what the obvious answer I'd of given to this would be.
<br />
On a little more thought, I had a better idea.
<br />
Yes, let people do it.
<br />
But it adds an extra tag to the characters name.
<br />

<br />
'E-bayed'
<br />

<br />
That way, you can see quite clearly who's done this, can put them on ignore, even maybe have a display filter so you don't have to acknowledge these people in the slightest.  Even better idea, give them a new server where gear is decided on your bank balance, not skill/time.  Call it the 'Smedly' server or something...
<br />

<br />
Good grief, if this actually was ever seriously considered...
<br />

<br />
(Pity there's not a customer EULA that disallows the company todo something they've stopped the player base doing).
<br />

<br />
Anyone remember that photoshopped pic with the ability to enter your CC details when you loot items?  Never thought it'd actually happen.
<br />

