				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The new poll, rl cash for in game objects....<a name="44124"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 4 04 8:44 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Whether deliberate or not, the poll explicitly states &quot;transfer items&quot; not accounts or characters... so for now I'll ignore the idea of selling characters. Actually, I'm less worried about selling whole characters than the selling of loot.
<br />

<br />
As mentioned above, once you can sell loot, then the existing issues with distributing loot suddenly multiply 100-fold. If someone ninja-loots an item they are effectively stealing real life money. Suddenly, it stops becoming a game. One roll of the dice could make you some nice RL money. Imagine the tension rolling on a BoC
<br />

<br />
NBG would go out the window. Gifting people valuable items (I gave a friend some ornate plate boots the other day) would almost completely stop. People will be viewed with suspicion that they are only bidding dkp on an item to sell it for $$ later.
<br />

<br />
I voted no. I have no idea why they'd make such a poll, I can only hope its a first phase to trying to stop IGE/Yantis. I can dream, can't I?<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
